<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-13T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="211" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d211">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.5045/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-13T14:00:00-05:00">December 13, 1929—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>113. All quiet. Damien Law and Medical School students still on strike;
                            special efforts have been made to induce medical students to return to
                            their school but so far without effect. Continuing efforts to start
                            rural farm schools and gradually all schools under the Service
                            Technique.</p>
                        <p>If conditions remain quiet I shall direct brigade commander to remove on
                            December 16th the restriction regarding circulation after 9 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>